ne marrow suppression occurs, treatment with leflunomide should be stopped and washout procedure administered.', 'Others', 'Concomitant use of leflunomide with other immuno- or myelosuppressive antirheumatic agents should generally be avoided.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/128683/', '', 'Antithymocyte immunoglobulin (rabbit), Tocilizumab, Secukinumab, Ravulizumab, Mycophenolic acid, Apremilast, Inebilizumab, Belumosudil, Belimumab, Emapalumab, Sutimlimab, More', 'Apremilast, Belumosudil, Leflunomide, Teprotumumab, Emapalumab, Ravulizumab, Pegcetacoplan, Eculizumab, Sutimlimab', 1767369485);
